                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b/88: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-27T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1922—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. Commercial Cable Company states Cortes is likely to adjourn early in July and
                    that unless form of concession for its landing rights at Azores is placed before
                    Cortes for ratification before it adjourns an indefinite delay will probably
                    result.</p>
                <p>Urgently request Portuguese Foreign Office to submit to the Company’s
                    representative a form of concession for the landing rights at the Azores which
                    it desires and endeavor to have concession submitted to Cortes for ratification
                    before it adjourns.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
